para_trans: To grant financial sanction for grant in aid to folk artists' troupes in the state for capital and experimentation expenses under the grant package during the financial year 2024-25.
Department of Tourism and Cultural Affairs,
Government Decision No. Janapada 4725 / P.No.21 (AD No.931692) / S.C.4
Madam Cama Road, Martyrdom Rajguru Chowk,
Read: - Department of Tourism and Cultural Affairs, Government Decisions, No. Popular 4725 /
Q. No.21 (AD No.931692) / Sec.4, D. 24th March, 2025.

Preamble: - With a view to encourage all folk arts in the state to survive, make these folk arts known to the next generation and preserve all traditional folk arts in Maharashtra as a whole, a scheme has been introduced under the Government Decision dated 1st January, 2008 of the Department to provide subsidy to the art teams for capital expenditure for costumes, musical instruments, costumes, materials, tent materials, electricity, acoustics and vehicles etc. as well as for experimentation. Capital and Experiment Grants to Folk Artists' Art Groups in this Financial Year 2024-2025
The amount has been granted administrative sanction under the above mentioned Government Decision. Now,
It was under the consideration of the government to grant financial sanction for the same.

Government Decision: - Under this Government Decision, a total of 35 Art Committees are being given financial sanction under the grant package to Folk Art Committees for the financial year 2024-2025 and 38 Art Committees are being given experimental grant amounting to a total amount of Rs. 1,04,00 000 / - (Rupees One Crore Four Lakh only) as per the statement given below.
